metadata.name: Lost in the attraction / abstraction #185
metadata.description:
This project is an experiment with a chaotic attractor, radial symmetry and some Perlin noise.

---
Features

Parts: the number of symmetrical parts (4|6|8|10)

Palette: the palette chosen to draw the sketch

Attractors incrementation: a number between 0.0013 and 0.003 which will increment the parameters (a, b, c & d) of an attractor (Clifford A. Pickover).

---
Resolutions & controls

By default the work is drawn on a canvas of 1280 x 1280 pixels but you can double or triple this resolution, for this in live mode add to the URL &scale= with the desired factor.

You can also download an image (PNG) by pressing [d] key.


---
This artwork celebrate the first anniversary of FxHash, 50% of the proceeds will go to the Processing Foundation.


Created with typescript and simplex-noise (npm package). 

Artwork by Nicolas Lebrun / @nclslbn / https://nicolas-lebrun.fr/contact/

metadata.name: Postcard from Amsterdam #147
metadata.description:
Hope you are ok.

I've been busy, doing ok. 
Autumn with some nice warmer days 
trees and leaves in colors

cycling / working 
I was on a ferry-boat this late afternoon,
amsterdam-north to the center
and some great clouds. colors and lightning 
when the sun went down

and sketching this week ^___^

playing with letters, calligraphy

had a big pile of words for a conceptual work

in the past, I used the source of a program
also for the visuals-text output on the screen
and now was thinking, using this concept text next, 
to create- (de)construct a 2D/3D world with it.

But man. words are so 'touchy' and triggering sometimes,
so deleted all offensive, negative, mood-triggering, distracting words, heh..
until I had some fine lorum-like shizzle to work with.


also wanted to make like a kind of 
digital (jungle) zen garden  -____-

was playing around in 
my 2D 3D sketch zen space


I wanted to do something with leaves,
that quickly turned into like a flock of birds

then also start using older 3D to 2D calculations
that turned into a kind of rail road - metro stop
then I thought that's a nice stop!


If we would ever encounter aliens
what kind of 'universal' language would we use
or would they use? 

Recently saw something on tv, - at a friends house
like these alien-shows on cable tv;
humans were ignored by this star-trek federation,
because we were 'not ready'.

Well I like to party at this cool planet in terra-omega-apha-yes-apha-whatever, 
with some nice nebula's around.
I have some cool 'earthy' dancin moves,  and can show some funky letters.
but  our 'leaders' messed up, making a big shit of this planet.
 
Now we are all universal outcasts.. 
lol. sos from earth. please help us keeping-make this 'a great universal paradise'! We have lovely nature, art, great music and dancing!


want to do something with travelling and animation
some crazy and fun movie ideas

I love to focus on
-and see the great 
and wonderful things in life as well

discover new 'blind spots'


want to wish you a wonderful week 

make friends with yourself
and be easy 
on yourself today
ok?

let the past go and flow

a shower to wake up
fresh clothing

create something
work that flow
make it funky again

move like an animal 
that knows kung-fu

xxx amsterdam chillout  0__.  ^__^ 

Nov 4, 2022

- vanilla javascript - a 'rgb+a' pixel engine - the work is 1 html file
- 'pure software' 2D - 3D drawing, 100% pixels baby!
- no webgl or shaders used
- Image composition - check; used some old 8x8 pixelfont/data of mine, no images are loaded
- Animated - builds up, cross between animation and still
- Interactive - mouseclick - you can zoom-in out with mouse (touch-phone is still messy somehow)
- s-key saves image, and also the top alpha image
- space - hide-show the top alpha layer-animation
- redraws after some time, because it's like a movie ticket.


thx..
fxhash & crew
friends and fans 
collectors, art-lovers, coders and artist 
you make it rock! keep the vibe alive!

to the kings of the underground
and to all people struggling, 
keep pushing it; turn it into art and dance

metadata.name: ASCII Graffiti #27
metadata.description:
ASCII Graffiti is my second project using only ASCII, font glyphs and UNICODE. Inspiration for this project came from train graffiti. I live close to multiple train crossings. Rather than be annoyed about the delay in my commute as they passed, I instead decided to snap photos of train graffiti. Train crossings became a little welcome art break rather than a inconvenience ðŸ˜Š. Colors and styles vary widely across my sampled graffiti art, but there were also some common themes and palettes that presented themselves. Iâ€™ve photographed everything from random scribbles to works that cover entire boxcars. I find some connectedness in train graffiti. All of us, in all walks of life, sitting at a train crossing watching the same train, the same art, pass us by. Sometimes thousands of miles apart, weâ€™re all really not so different. 

For this project, each of the color schemes (15) were chosen based on IRL graffiti art. Some artists used bright and vivid colors, while others were more monochromatic. My goal here was to create art that is easy to print and display, so I focused on using a plain white background to allow collectors to print on whatever paper type they prefer. I prefer printing on textured paper for whatever reason. 

Output: PNG
Canvas Size: 4800 X 6000 at 300 dpi
Color Schemes: 15
Date: January 2023

Coded in p5.js

metadata.name: Handachak #110
metadata.description:
I have always been looking for solutions that can connect different visual elements in such a way as to create an integrated system and structure and each part of the work plays its own role in this system.
Another point is that always attributing physical characteristics to abstract forms creates aesthetic qualities. From a general point of view, one of these features is perspective, and in this project we see a type of perspective in an abstract and geometric structure.
"Handachak" means "Geometry" in ancient Persian.

metadata.name: Eikonal identities #9
metadata.description:
Works in the invisible
Inevitable shadows
Digital exorcism
Silicon catharsis


Eikonal
- Usually "eikonal equation" : the wave-like description of the propagation of light through a medium
- In optics, relative to the formation of an image
- anagram : e-kaolin



-----
* What/How *

Product of the code.

A picture generated by a succession of chaotic events applied to a system of 4.2 million particles.
The drawing process consists of mixing and projecting the particles randomly in space.

Each image is unique and depends only on the address of minter's wallet and current iteration number.

-----
* Technics *

- Hand written code in Javascript, GLSL
- Uses three.js library, WebGL particles, physics
- Generates a FullHD PNG (1080x1080 px bitmap 24bits)
- Takes less than 15 seconds of generation on a relatively recent GPU (>2017)

-----

metadata.name: pang #79
metadata.description:
Within each of us resides an evolutionary history of primal emotions, yet we often spend our lives dulling and controlling these instincts rather than reveling in them. Art is one of the ways we best express those instincts and intuitions â€“ accessing and visualizing their visceral qualities, and releasing our deepest emotions in a way we can share.

pang reflects emotions that take control of our impulses â€“ anguish, euphoria, obsession. By using crayon-like marks, the artworks convey the catharsis felt while drawing with a childlike abandon. To capture what gives such marks true feeling, the works deliberate the intrinsic movements, pressures, and angles shaped by hands in various moods. These qualities and their frenetic meanderings represent the infinite possibilities of where the crayon could go next â€“ if only we could free ourselves from the layers of control we've built.

The contradictions we struggle with are reflected throughout the works:  in the long, methodical, and mathematical path to creation that yields work that looks fast, free and unrehearsed;  through the randomly-informed computer generation of art that feels human;  and by the depiction of long-standing traditional techniques to help display the conceptual range of a young, innovative art movement still establishing its pivotal place in the canon of art. These tensions parallel the work's underlying concept, accentuating the suspicion that a learned fear of emotional expression might just be the source of our own pang. 

Created in p5.js, pang is inspired by the emotional works and processes of later abstract expressionists such as Cy Twombly and Joan Mitchell â€“ as well as contemporary artists like JosÃ© Parla.

Functionality: 
Press â€˜pâ€™ to save as a png. 
Press â€˜bâ€™ to render with (or without) a transparent background.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality.  0 (lowest quality) to 9 (highest quality, 15000 pixels lengthwise).
Press â¬†ï¸ (arrow up) to incrementally increase pixel density.
Press â¬‡ï¸ (arrow down) to incrementally decrease pixel density.

__________
TENDER x abstractment
April 2022

metadata.name: simple things #292
metadata.description:
Thereâ€™s beauty in simple things. Sunlight. A reflection on a puddle. The flight of a bird. Observing the clouds. Spending time with loved ones.

To celebrate the re-opening of fxhash, I'd like to contribute with some simple thing to enjoy among friends who rejoin after some time.

Simple things is a piece that is just that: simple things. Nothing fancy here. Simple circles doing simple movement, with simple colours. Maybe the viewer will rejoice in observing them transit on the screen.

It has some controls: you can press â€œsâ€ to save a png file. You can set a higher resolution pressing â€œdâ€ followed by 1-9 to increase pixel density (if you get a black image, press â€œd 0â€ and start again with a lower number). Simple controls.

It has also colour controls: press z for brightness, x for contrast, g for gamma, b for blur, n for noise followed by + or - to alter their values. You might get some simple variations that you might enjoy. Press a to enable/disable all colour controls (except the noise).

The pieces exhibit simple variations: palettes, circle sizes, density of elements, backgrounds. The colours might be inverted sometimes. The direction of the movement changes also in some pieces. Some are grayscale pieces.

Just like in life, enjoying simple things is sometimes enough to leave behind the noise and our worries. Also like in life, if one wants something extra, they may get it by looking for it...

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-RodrÃ­guez, @msoriaro.
Made in p5.js, and glsl for the image controls.

metadata.name: Anachronous #189
metadata.description:
This project is about the exploration of chaotic structures created with lines and blurry silhouettes. They work together to make the shapes emerge without revealing them completely and create dark and light areas that compose a feeling of depth and weight to the scene.

Some pieces are chaotic, some more ordered. Some have strong compositions, some don't. By zooming in on the details we can let our mind wander and start seeing shapes.

Best experienced in full-screen.

Press S to take a screenshot
Press M to take a high resolution screenshot
Press H to take a higher resolution screenshot (may not work for some devices)

WARNING: Project is using webgl, it may not work on some older devices.

Original artwork by William Watkins Â· Lyon, 2022
